<details>
  <summary>Understanding HSL(A) ðŸ“–</summary>
  <p>
    <strong>Hue</strong> is the color type, like red, green, or blue. It is a number between
    <code>0</code> and <code>360</code> degrees.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Saturation</strong> is the intensity of the color. It is a number between
    <code>0</code> and <code>100</code> percent. Optional, default <code>100</code>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Lightness</strong> is the brightness of the color. It is a number between
    <code>0</code> and <code>100</code> percent. Optional, default <code>50</code>.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Alpha</strong> is the transparency of the color. It is a number between
    <code>0</code> and <code>1</code>. Optional, default <code>1</code>.
  </p>
</details>
